<inglise> The Hearing Officer shall seek to ensure in particular that in the preparation of draft Commission decisions in competition cases due account is taken of all the relevant facts, whether favourable or unfavourable to the parties concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> &Auml;rakuulamise eest vastutav ametnik p&uuml;&uuml;ab eelk&otilde;ige hoolitseda selle eest, et konkurentsi k&auml;sitlevate komisjoni otsuste eeln&otilde;ude koostamisel v&otilde;etakse n&otilde;uetekohaselt arvesse k&otilde;ik asjakohased faktid, olenemata sellest, kas need on asjaosalistele soodsad v&otilde;i ebasoodsad. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> In performing his duties the Hearing Officer shall see to it that the rights of the defence are respected, while taking account of the need for effective application of the competition rules in accordance with the regulations in force and the principles laid down by the Court of First Instance and the Court of Justice. </inglise>
<eesti> Oma kohustuste t&auml;itmisel j&auml;lgib &auml;rakuulamise eest vastutav ametnik, et peetaks kinni &otilde;igusest kaitsele, v&otilde;ttes arvesse seejuures konkurentsieeskirjade t&otilde;husa rakendamise vajadust kehtivate m&auml;&auml;ruste ja esimese astme kohtu ja Euroopa Kohtu poolt kehtestatud p&otilde;him&otilde;tete kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
